System Design:
=================

System design is the blueprint of a software system. defines system architecture, components, interfaces and data flows.
focus on scalability, reliability, performance and maintainability. Converts business requirements into technical architecture.
establishes clear boundaries between databases, users and services. balances functionalities with operational realities.

Why is system design important?
===================================

Scalability & reliability -> Ensures system handles millions of requests without failure.
Architectural thinking -> goes beyond coding. Involves trade-off like SQL vs NOSQL, cap theorem.
Career growth -> Essential for becoming a senior engineer or architect.
Real world problem solving -> helps in building actual systems not just clearing interviews.
Trade-offs & decision making -> Balances scalability, cost, speed, and complexity.
Future proofing ->  prevents bottlenecks and allows smooth evolution of software.

Evolution of system design over 25 years
============================================

1. 1995 -2005 => Early monolithic web applications

LAMP Stack (Linux, Apache , MySQL, PHP) dominated.
stateless servers, single node databases, basic MVC architectures
server side rendering, no real time features.

2. 2005 - 2010 => Scaling challenges and distributed systems

Social media, ecommerce drove demand for better performance.
Intrductions caching(Redis, memcached),CDNs, database replication.
Horizontal scaling and load balancing become standard.

3. 2010 - 2015 => The cloud revolution

AWS, Azure, GCP enabled on demand infrastruture scalability.
Shift to virtualized & containerized deployments.
NoSQL databases (Cassandra, MongoDB) gained popularity.

4. 2015 - 2020 => Microservices and event driven architecture.

Monoliths evolved into microservices for agility.
CI/CD pipeleines streamlined software delivery.
APi gateways, Service meshes, Event driven systems (Kafka, RabbitMQ).

5. 2020 - Present => Real time, AI- driven , edge computing

focus on low latency (streaming, AI driven recommendations)
serveless computing, kubernetes and edge computing growth
increased emphasis on security, complaince and observability.

